{
  "stem": "1033.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That we were handed soaps that said RIF, [GERMAN] soap.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It didn't form.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was kind of gunk.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We didn't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I guess the Germans hadn't left anything underutilized.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Anyhow, we were put in this block and people kept coming.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I discovered that my grandmother's oldest brother and her younger brother were both in this camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the oldest brother was in charge of the disinfectant unit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And remarkably, this man-- his name was [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Shandar ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Vol, ?]-- always referred to me as [INAUDIBLE] grandson-- never by my name.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE], of course, was his sister.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I was the first grandson.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So now I get a bit of reflected glory half a century later.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Auschwitz was dreadful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was very cold in the morning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "At 5 o'clock in the morning, we had shouts of [GERMAN], which means coffee time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was kind of a black slop that I-- I had acid stomach.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I remember standing for hours spitting into a can because the saliva kept coming up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I still have a very poor stomach.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It's a miracle that I survived.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I hope it's going to last for a while.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Auschwitz-- after standing for hours-- they were called appels.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "We were counted five deep.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "People came and counted us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And then we were discharged.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Then often, somebody started shouting 'oven' because the mornings were very cold.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we stood against one another for heat.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And there we stood.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And I remember once somebody decided, let's say the [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We really said it out loud, everybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I remember the sky as grey as grey can be.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And that was nothing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "There were certainly no acknowledgements of any kind coming forth.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
